title: Pokémon: Master Quest
description: With the Olivine City Gym temporarily out of commission, our heroes are off to the Whirl Cup Competition—and Misty wants in on the action! Resuming their journey, they find that Jessie, James, and Meowth aren’t the only members of Team Rocket they need to worry about, though that dastardly trio still has a few tricks up their collective sleeve. After a heated battle with the final Gym Leader, Ash moves on to the Silver Conference, but does he have the mettle to take on his old rival, Gary?

media.title: Around the Whirlpool
media.description: In a scuffle with Team Rocket, Ash and friends are thrown from the ship bearing them to the Whirl Islands! Can they escape the powerful whirlpools that threaten to drag them down?

media.title: Fly Me to the Moon
media.description: The Pidgey on a protected island don’t have to worry about being attacked, so most have lost interest in flying. But one of them still dreams of soaring beyond the stars! Can Ash and friends help?

media.title: Takin' It on the Chinchou
media.description: Our heroes pass a small mountain village just in time for the annual Chinchou migration. The village always sends Trainers to protect the Chinchou on their journey—but will they be enough to stop Team Rocket?

media.title: A Corsola Caper
media.description: When a family’s home is threatened by the Corsola who live nearby, it’s Ash and friends to the rescue…and maybe Misty can finally catch that Corsola she’s been after!

media.title: Mantine Overboard
media.description: After our heroes miss a ferry, they meet a diver who offers to take them to the next island…but they’re soon distracted by tales of treasure aboard a sunken ship!

media.title: Octillery the Outcast
media.description: When they’re not competing in the Whirl Cup, Ash and Misty try to help a young Trainer whose Octillery has been rejected by its Remoraid friends after evolving.

media.title: Dueling Heroes
media.description: After winning their preliminary rounds, Ash and Misty face formidable opponents in the Whirl Cup. Meanwhile, the Team Rocket trio have their eyes on stealing the tournament’s prize!

media.title: The Perfect Match
media.description: It’s the second round of the Whirl Cup, and Ash and Misty have been paired up against each other! Who will come out on top? And will Team Rocket’s plan to distract the police be successful?

media.title: Plant It Now… Diglett Later
media.description: Our heroes are asked to help protect a village from marauders who threaten to make off with the Diglett who live there—and thanks to a delicious dinner, Team Rocket offers to help, too!

media.title: Hi Ho Silver… Away!
media.description: Our heroes meet a jewelry maker who tells them the legend of the fourth Whirl Island…and who soon finds himself embroiled in a Team Rocket plot!

media.title: The Mystery Is History
media.description: While two sets of Team Rocket villains set out to capture the Legendary Pokémon Lugia, Ash runs into his old friend Richie and his partner, a Pikachu named Sparky!

media.title: A Parent Trapped
media.description: The little Lugia named Silver has fallen into the hands of Butch and Cassidy of Team Rocket, and with Richie's help, Ash must win the adult Lugia’s trust before it gets caught in the same trap!

media.title: A Promise Is a Promise
media.description: While trying to rescue the two Lugia from Team Rocket, Ash and friends have been taken prisoner! Now, they must figure out a way to escape…and to free the captured Pokémon as well!

media.title: Throwing In the Noctowl
media.description: Ash and friends are on a plane back to Olivine City when they get caught in a terrible storm that also sweeps up Team Rocket’s balloon! They’ll have to work together to land safely…but can they manage it?

media.title: Nerves of Steelix
media.description: After several interruptions, including yet another Team Rocket scheme, Ash’s battle against Jasmine at the Olivine Gym is finally getting under way!

media.title: Bulbasaur… the Ambassador!
media.description: When the Pokémon at Professor Oak's lab in Kanto have a hard time getting along, the professor asks Ash to send his Bulbasaur to the lab so it can help keep the peace.

media.title: Espeon, Not Included
media.description: In Ecruteak City, our heroes meet up with their friend Sakura and her newly evolved Espeon. Sakura and her sisters are preparing for a dance competition, but Team Rocket is lurking in the wings, hoping to steal their Pokémon…

media.title: For Ho-Oh the Bells Toll
media.description: When our heroes investigate a sudden pealing of bells, they discover that the Crystal Bells, which are said to ring only when the Legendary Pokémon Ho-Oh returns, are missing! The researcher Eusine seems to know something…

media.title: Extreme Pokémon
media.description: When Ash runs into his old rival Gary preparing to enter his Arcanine in a race, he decides to compete as well! But first, he’ll have to chase Team Rocket away from the Pokémon Day Care.

embed_url.title: An Egg-Sighting Adventure
embed_url.description: The egg—yet to hatch—that Ash had received from a grateful Pokemon breeder turns up missing.

embed_url.title: Hatching a Plan
embed_url.description: At long last Ash's egg hatches, a Phanpy emerging to finally put everyone's curiosity to rest. Ash and friends' excitement is matched only by that of Jessie and James of Team Rocket.

embed_url.title: Dues and Don'ts
embed_url.description: As Jessie, James, and Meowth track Ash and friends, they commiserate over past failures and discuss how they are paired unfairly against these younger trainers with such a superior array of Pokémon.

embed_url.title: Just Waiting on a Friend
embed_url.description: Our heroes are traveling over a mountain pass when inclement weather occasions a stay in a lodge located conveniently nearby.

embed_url.title: Fit to be Tyrogued
embed_url.description: Ash and friends chance into a Tyrogue, nearly falling victim to a ploy it lays out in an attempt to make off with all of their Pokémon food.

embed_url.title: Xatu the Future
embed_url.description: Ash and friends meet a Xatu, a Pokémon said to have the ability to see into the future.

embed_url.title: Talkin' 'bout an Evolution
embed_url.description: Ash and friends discover a red Gyarados, unknowingly uncovering a plot by Team Rocket to control the secrets of Pokémon evolution.

embed_url.title: The Rage of Innocence
embed_url.description: Before they can oppose Team Rocket's evil plan to gain control of the Pokémon of the world, Ash and friends must escape from a Team Rocket holding pen.

embed_url.title: As Cold as Pryce
embed_url.description: Finally setting foot in Mahogany Town, Ash is anxious to set about winning his next badge.

embed_url.title: Nice Pryce, Baby
embed_url.description: Having earned Pryce's respect and permission to face the trainer in a gym battle, Ash makes the unlikely choice of sending out Cyndaquil, a Fire Pokémon, to face his opponent on an Ice battlefield.

embed_url.title: Whichever Way the Wind Blows
embed_url.description: Hardly taking a second to relish his latest gym victory, Ash quickly sets course for the next gym in Blackthorn City.

embed_url.title: Some Like It Hot
embed_url.description: Ash, Misty, and Brock face many roadblocks on the path to success, some metaphoric and others in the form of gigantic Magcargo that refuse to step aside and let a traveler pass.

embed_url.title: Hocus Pokémon
embed_url.description: Brock rarely meets a girl whom he doesn't find bewitching, but on encountering a particular young woman, even Ash and Misty can't deny that there is something magical about her.

embed_url.title: As Clear as Crystal
embed_url.description: When a tangle with Team Rocket leaves Pikachu desperately exhausted, a young passerby offers to restore Pikachu's energy.

embed_url.title: Same Old Song and Dance
embed_url.description: In the midst of their travels, Ash and friends meet up with a young girl who, along with her two Igglybuff assistants, stars in her own musical variety television program.

embed_url.title: Enlighten Up
embed_url.description: As Ash and friends approach the site where Ash will earn his eighth badge, they fall victim to an unexpected Team Rocket trap.

embed_url.title: Will the Real Oak Please Stand Up?
embed_url.description: Hearing of the posh reception prepared for the host and guest of a radio show to be recorded before a live audience, Jessie and James of Team Rocket quickly announce that they are in fact the long-awaited celebrities.

embed_url.title: Wish Upon a Star Shape
embed_url.description: Ash, Misty, and Brock are traveling along when they notice a strange shape falling from the sky. They run in to investigate, but soon realized that they were not the only witnesses of this event.

embed_url.title: Outrageous Fortunes
embed_url.description: On meeting up with a proud Pokémon trainer who dares all comers to face his Poliwrath, Misty and Ash quickly rise to the challenge.

embed_url.title: One Trick Phony
embed_url.description: Seeing that Ash just can't get enough battling, a trainer who loses to him suggests as she leaves that he give a local Pokémon battle park a try.

embed_url.title: I Politoed Ya So
embed_url.description: When Ash, Misty, and Brock pause for a quaint picnic by a lake, Politoed wanders off and is mistaken by another trainer for her own Politoed, the rhythm leader in her Pokémon cheerleading squad that had gone AWOL.

embed_url.title: Beauty is Skin Deep
embed_url.description: Finally reaching the outskirts of Blackthorn City, Ash pushes to quickly seek out the gym where he hopes to earn his final Johto badge.

embed_url.title: Fangs For Nothing
embed_url.description: No sooner has Ash begun what he hopes will be his final gym battle in the Johto League than Team Rocket once again throws a wrench into his plans, making off with the Dragon Fang.

embed_url.title: Great Bowls of Fire
embed_url.description: Immediately after entering an area considered sacrosanct by the Dragon Pokémon that dwell there, Team Rocket sets off a chain of events that enrages the area's Dragonite guardian.

embed_url.title: Better Eight Than Never
embed_url.description: Having finally seen stability restored to the Blackthorn Gym, Ash and Claire face off in a gym battle.

embed_url.title: Why? Wynaut
embed_url.description: Having defeated Clair and earned his eighth gym badge, Ash must now set out for the Johto League championship, which he learns is to be held on Mt Silver in three months time.

embed_url.title: Just Add Water
embed_url.description: On the road back to New Bark Town, Ash and friends stop for a rest near the ocean. There they spot a sign advertising a synchronized Pokémon swimming event.

embed_url.title: Lapras of Luxury
embed_url.description: Ash and friends return to New Bark Town, Professor Elm sends him on an errand to retrieve a Pokémon egg from a nearby marine Pokémon laboratory.

embed_url.title: Hatch Me If You Can
embed_url.description: Questions as to what Pokémon waits inside the egg Ash and friends have been carrying for Professor Elm are finally answered when it hatches into a Larvitar.

embed_url.title: Entei at Your Own Risk
embed_url.description: As Ash and friends continue their travels with Larvitar, it remains wary of all other Pokémon and people, particularly of Misty.

embed_url.title: A Crowning Achievement
embed_url.description: Brock leads Ash and Misty toward a beautiful lake he has read about in his guidebook, but when they arrive at its supposed location, they find nothing but a dried-up stream, surrounded by a number of thirsty Slowpoke.

embed_url.title: Here's Lookin' at You, Elekid
embed_url.description: A troublesome Elekid begins harassing Larvitar only moments before Team Rocket swoops in and captures both rare Pokémon in a high-tensile steel net.

embed_url.title: You're a Star, Larvitar
embed_url.description: Ash and friends report back to Professor Elm as they reach the base of Mount Silver, where they hope to return their Larvitar to its birthplace.

embed_url.title: Address Unown!
embed_url.description: A strange energy is emitted from the sky and an Unown pops out, landing right on Misty's head!

embed_url.title: Mother of All Battles
embed_url.description: Now that they have finally gaining Larvitar's trust, the group head towards the Pokémon Reserve on Mt. Silver, as led by Larvitar.

embed_url.title: Pop Goes the Sneasel
embed_url.description: With Larvitar returned to its rightful home, Ash and company make their way to Silver Town for the Silver Conference Tournament.

embed_url.title: A Claim to Flame!
embed_url.description: Gary is set on entering the Silver Conference, and is determined that this time he will be able to make it all the way, and beat Ash!

embed_url.title: Love, Pokémon Style
embed_url.description: Ash begins the Silver Conference Tournament in Division H against two opponents.

embed_url.title: Tie One On!
embed_url.description: As the Johto League Silver Conference gets underway, Ash will take on Jackson from New Bark Town. Ash is looking forward to the match, but perhaps not as much as his Bulbasaur.

embed_url.title: The Ties That Bind
embed_url.description: Ash is about to take on his long time rival, Gary Oak, in the next battle of the Johto League Silver Conference, and he's determined to do everything he can to win.

embed_url.title: Can't Beat the Heat
embed_url.description: Our hero is in the middle of the first match of the championship tournament at the Johto League Silver Conference. His opponent is his long time rival—Gary Oak.

embed_url.title: Playing with Fire!
embed_url.description: Ash is battling Harrison from Hoenn at the Johto League Silver Conference. It's a close match the whole way through, but one by one Harrison knocks out Totodile, Snorlax, and Noctowl.

embed_url.title: Johto Photo Finish
embed_url.description: The scorching battle between Ash and Harrison rages on, with Charizard taking on Blaziken, a Pokémon from the Hoenn region!

embed_url.title: Gotta Catch Ya Later!
embed_url.description: With the Johto League Silver Conference behind them, Ash, Brock and Misty head back to Viridian City to relax.

embed_url.title: Hoenn Alone!
embed_url.description: Ash has left all of his Pokémon behind in Pallet Town—except Pikachu—and boarded a ship bound for Littleroot Town in Hoenn. Unfortunately, Team Rocket is on board as well.
